summary:"Nuno Loureiro was the theorist who cracked magnetic reconnection — the fundamental plasma physics problem standing between humanity and working fusion energy — and the director of the most important fusion research laboratory in the Western world. He was shot dead at his Brookline home on December 15, 2025 by a former university classmate from Portugal who drove from Florida specifically to kill him. In four video confessions, the killer gave no motive. SPARC — the device Loureiro shepherded — was targeting net-positive fusion energy in 2027. He was killed weeks before its planned first plasma.",
