summary:"Carl Grillmair, 67, research scientist at Caltech's IPAC, ran quality assurance on the NEOWISE Science Data Center and was validating NEO Surveyor's instrument performance — the spacecraft designed to find asteroids before they hit Earth. He contributed to the discovery of water on a distant planet. He was found shot on the front porch of his rural Llano home at 6 a.m. on February 16, 2026. What makes this more than a rural homicide: suspect Freddy Snyder, 29, had previously been arrested for trespassing on Grillmair's property while carrying a rifle. Those charges were dismissed. He then allegedly returned and killed Grillmair. Armed trespass — release — murder. That sequence is documented court record, reported by the LA Times and ABC7.",
