summary:"Two sitting US Congressmen have now publicly raised the cluster of scientist deaths and disappearances documented in this timeline. Rep. Tim Burchett (R-TN) stated that if the public knew what he had been briefed on regarding extraterrestrial matters, people would be 'up at night' and the country would come 'unglued.' He explicitly named McCasland and Reza as non-coincidental. And he stated, for the public record: 'I'm not suicidal.' Rep. Eric Burlison (R-MO) formally requested FBI involvement, calling the pattern 'deeply concerning,' and stated: 'It's remarkable that General McCasland apparently walked out of his home, left all of his devices and never came back. And Monica Reza, she was on a hike as well and mysteriously disappeared. And I've heard of others.' Burchett put the broader effect plainly: 'This has had a real chilling effect. People don't want to talk about this issue of Unidentified Flying Objects anymore, and it's kind of difficult to get to people because they are afraid.'",
